description:
The best gaming tech at CES 2025 included Razer’s Project Arielle, a heating and cooling gaming chair, MSI’s Coreliquid cooler concept, and the Lenovo Legion GO S handheld. The Roto VR Explorer brought motion to VR with its rotating chair, LG’s 5k2k bendable monitor offered flexible visuals, and the Atari Gamestation Go combined retro fun with modern design.

title: Best Gaming Tech at CES 2025

author: Cybernews
description:
During CES 2025 Day 2, we came across some cool tech, like the Reborock Saros Z70, a vacuum with a built-in arm, the Ray-Ban Meta Smart Glasses, and Razer’s Project Arielle, the world’s first gaming chair with heating and cooling. Other highlights included MSI’s super cute CORELIQUID Cooler concept, a $500 motorised drivable carry-on luggage, and the Rotoverse Roto VR Explorer, a virtual reality chair that rotates for a fully immersive experience.
